# SSH keys allowed to sign commits for Rocicorp pull requests.
#
# This file is consumed by the Verify Signed Commit Authors action in this
# repository.
# It uses Git's gpg.ssh.allowedSignersFile / OpenSSH allowed_signers format.
#
# Each active line authorizes one public key:
#
#   <signer-principal> namespaces="git" <ssh-key-type> <base64-public-key> <comment>
#
# test
#
# Example:
#
#   alice@example.com namespaces="git" ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAI... alice-laptop-2026
#
# Notes:
#
# - Add public keys only. Never add private keys.
# - Keep namespaces="git" so the key is scoped to Git SSH signatures.
# - The principal should match the identity the signer uses for Git commit
#   signing, commonly their GitHub noreply email or work email.
# - OpenSSH validity options such as valid-after and valid-before can be used
#   during key rotation, for example:
#
#     alice@example.com namespaces="git",valid-after="2026-01-01T00:00:00Z" ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3... alice-laptop-2026
#
# ========================================================================
# TEAM ACTION REQUIRED
#
# Add the team's SSH commit-signing PUBLIC KEYS below this block.
#
# The allow-list is intentionally empty for now because the public keys are
# not available at the time this file is being added. Until at least one
# non-comment allowed_signers entry is added below, the signed-commit-author
# action will find this file successfully but reject every PR commit.
#
# Put one key per line below, using the format shown above.
